The AArch64 CPU interpreter, the device models (virtio-mmio, fw_cfg, PSCI,
GICv2, PL011, PL031, virtio-blk/net/console/9p), and the user-mode network
stack are original implementations. They interoperate with the QEMU "virt"
platform, EDK2 firmware, and the Linux kernel by targeting those projects'
public hardware and software interfaces; no third-party source code is
included or distributed with this project.

src/fdt/virt.dts (and its compiled form src/fdt/virt_dtb.h) is a device-tree
blob generated by QEMU for the "virt" machine, with seeds zeroed for
reproducibility. It is functional hardware-description data, not part of the
Apache-licensed source, and carries no separate copyright claim.
